            <abstract label="Abstract:">Business records, 1932-1956, most from the Boston office
                &amp; centering on information about ramie. Includes correspondence, all concerning
                ramie; some letters discuss decortication &amp; degumming of the fibers. Also a file
                of information about ramie, and folders of samples of ramie twine, some of which was
                made in Switzerland &amp; tested by the Plymouth Cordage Co.</abstract>
            <langmaterial label="Language:">Collection material in <language encodinganalog="MARC 041" langcode="eng">English</language>
            </langmaterial>
        <physdesc><extent>0.25 cubic feet</extent></physdesc></did>
        <bioghist encodinganalog="MARC 545">
            <head id="a5" altrender="organizational history">ORGANIZATIONAL HISTORY </head>
            <p>E.A. Shaw &amp; Co., cotton merchants &amp; raw materials dealers with offices in Los
                Angeles and Boston.</p>
        </bioghist>
        <scopecontent encodinganalog="MARC 520">
            <head id="a3">COLLECTION DESCRIPTION</head>
            <p>Collection mostly from the Boston office and centering on information about ramie, a
                fiber obtained from the bark of the ramie plant. Includes correspondence, 1932-1933,
                1948-1949, and 1954, all concerning ramie; some letters discuss decortication and
                degumming of the fibers. Also includes a file of information, 1956, about ramie; and
                folders of samples of ramie twine, including some made in Switzerland and tested by
                the Plymouth Cordage Co.</p>
        </scopecontent>
        <custodhist encodinganalog="MARC 582">
            <head id="a7" altrender="provenance">PROVENANCE: </head>
            <p>American Textile History Museum Collection, gift of Gordon Shaw.</p>
        </custodhist>
